\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did anyone outside the home help your other look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What about when she had a confinement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 We usually generally had a neighbour in. Mm. They used to do it for one another you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there a woman in the district who specialized in confinements at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - no, your aunt did, but not round where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did your mother have a proper nurse in when the children were born? She didn't have a local woman who sort of did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, I suppose a nurse came in, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember the birth of your youngest brother or younger sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - I remember it happening but it was during the night see, I wouldn't - when we got up in the morning it was - all over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you know at that time that there was a baby on the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes. I was fourteen yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did any of the relations, the aunts for example live near by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 The other side of London I think you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - our - both our parents really were - all friends together sort of thin
g if you see what I mean. Neighbours and friends but apart from that - they - different ones I suppose that - father worked with but apart from that they never had - any particular friends that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Your parents were friendly with your husband's parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 This started because they lived next door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 They didn't meet people and get to know them like you do for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 They weren't friendships that arose through other situations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Neighbours were friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You don't remember anybody who was not a neighbour and who was not a relation who they were friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did your husband's parents ever come in for a cup of tea or a meal or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well, I used to have - party tonight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid294263\charrsid527797 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 s together and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Joined together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 At Christmas time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm, and - parties that his - people used to give. And they had lots of parties, yes because they had - she -
 your mother had nephews in the Navy when they came home on leave and all that you see, you had parties. Then they'd all be together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did they ever go out together as a foursome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. They went on holiday together didn't they. The four of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Even in those years, before the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well yes, that was - no, that was just after the war. Just after the war that was, 1918. Left me in charge of - all the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 How many was that? Quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Five of mine and four of his. Thre
e of yours, you - you went with your - aunt didn't you. Four. Grace and Charlie, Liza and Vernon. I had two babies, they weren't at school - Vernon and Willie, they were both - under five. Nine I had. And I was about eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did your husband's mother sort of come in and chat with your mother in the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 They were in each other's houses a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 But were other neighbours on that same footing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 There weren't a lot of neighbours that she would call in on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, oh no, it did - she didn't believe in that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 These were really rather special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did your father ever bring any of his work friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh at times, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 For what sort of occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - don't know, just pop in I suppose. No, I suppose pop in for a drink and - wife now and again of the - man.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 When your husband's parents came in would there be a sort of invitation or would they just call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, just go in I suppose, as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 There wasn't any kind of formal invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 When your parents and your husband's parents got together and that sort of thing did they have music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - yes - well they - mostly only had gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid294263\charrsid527797 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 phone but they used to play a lot of cards together, your dad - the two dads. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What game did they play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Crib. Most of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did the women play too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would that be sometimes in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, and sometimes in theirs. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Could you tell me what you remember when you were a young girl the different social classes were as you remember them at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well, I don't think there was any just - as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Different social classes, you don't remember being aware that everybody wasn't in the same social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No. No. Not really. I don't think there was such a thing in those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 We were talking about how your father was a lot better off than some people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, but - they didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Other people of course were a lot better off than he was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, but they didn't seem to live any differently did they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You weren}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid294263\charrsid527797 \rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797  aware of the fact that other people had houses full of servants and carriages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, well you wouldn't be round that way. They all - all that - all in the working class you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 But you knew those people existed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Well - yes, I suppose you did, but - but - you was only conscious of the fact that - some people - when they left school went as servants to these p
eople, as maids and that. Apart from that you wouldn't - you wouldn't know how they lived. And of course then they wouldn't be around that area you see, you'd have to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would you say you were brought up to treat people all the same or treat some people differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Well, all the same but you had to treat - people with respect. And - my mother was very particular - you know, I mean - be sir - sir this and sir that you know to different people, which really was - a bit stupid I suppose when you come to think of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It was important to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What about your father, did he think that was important too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, he didn't bother. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What sort of people did she feel it was important for you to say sir to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh anybody, anybody really. She used to sir the baker and the butcher, anybody really. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What about a labourer, somebody like that who had less money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm. No, she didn't mind I don't suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 She'd call everybody sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - no
t everybody, but - traders she was - no, I suppose just - who she came in contact with, as far as I can remember. And we had to - and she bought us up to be very honest, because if we - brought the wrong change, you know, too much money we'd have to take 
it back. We weren't allowed to - keep it or anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 If there'd been a mistake made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, we'd have to take it back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember if there was anybody that you had to call madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember anybody calling your mother madam or your father sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Who were the most important people in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Where you lived were there some people that you think perhaps had a bit more respect than others, were looked up to a bit more fo
r one reason or another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I shouldn't think that, such as doctors and things like that naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there a doctor who lived in the Custom House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. Oh the - yes, he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 He was a clergyman was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Church of England, or Roman Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Were you brought up to sort of look up to certain people or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm - well no, not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. You were, you were to - shopkeepers - your 
schoolmaster, your teacher. Oh, people like that, your schoolmasters and teachers, because - well - you really had to respect all your elders. All - so it applied to everybody that was older than yourself you see.</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Even a kind of young adult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, you had to respect your elders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 That's not like that nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh good gracious no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you have to wait 'til they spoke to you, what from did this respect take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - you wouldn't - sort of - be rude to them like - chi
ldren are today, I mean - supposing you - you did anything wrong, and - they told you off, well you couldn't answer them back like children do today, they almost - they're really rude to you aren't they, majority of children. But that wouldn't be allowed 
would it. The same as at school, I mean, even with your teachers you wouldn't - they were very strict and you'd get the cane for - least little thing wouldn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 This clergyman that your husband mentioned, do you remember him calling on people, did he ever call round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr. K. Not on - us, but he used to.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did he not call on you because you were chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No, well of course anyway the - his church was a long way from us really wasn't it. Yes, I suppose he was round that way, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You don't remember him calling on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. Oh wait a - we used to have them - from our own chapel. I was going to say, he belonged to Beckton Road. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Can you remember was there a Church of England quite near where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, I went to Church of England school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 And the church was by the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would you say that you remembered that there was any difference between the type of person who went to church and who went to chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there a Salvation Army around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, there was a - a Salvation Army near us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there any difference between the type of person who went there and went to the chapel or the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 They didn't seem to be poorer people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Where you lived would you say all the people had the same standard of living or were there different levels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, was different levels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you think that one group of people felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well I suppose tradesmen's children and that would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 By tradesmen you mean the shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid294263\charrsid527797 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 keeping trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What about any distinction between craftsmen and labourers, people with a trade, skilled men and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You don't remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember that some families were thought to be rough and others respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 OH yes, definitely. Yes. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Can you tell me what at that time a rough family would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well - some o
f the children would be really spiteful wouldn't they, that type of child you know, and swear and all that sort of thing, that's what you would call rough and - Yes, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Loud, loud voices and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would a rough family usually be a poorer family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Not necessarily, no. Most of 'em were I dare say but wasn't necessary, no, just the way they're brought up I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 How was it you actually came into contact with these people, was it through work? Or did they live nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mr K. Well - my - my mother had got - two - a sister and a yes, my mother had got a sister and a brother, they lived in a road - street called Wightman Street, and it was a notorious street, and - the houses that they lived in was three rooms upstair
s, three rooms downstairs. Now my uncle had eleven children, and they lived in - they had - two bedrooms, and a kit - kitchen what they - lived in and a scullery. And all those children were brought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid294263\charrsid527797  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 up - in the house, and that house was - poorly furnished,
 but it was beautifully and clean on the floors and the tables with the - no lino or carpets. Mm. But they was beautifully washed clean and white. And - that's where I saw a lot of the experience of these people that - used to go out at night to - up the 
c
orner there and get drunk and come home and - and they'd fight. And the young daughters or sons - used to be murders there - police sent for and they'd come down or - and - there was one particular policeman, of course - he was in that area - he was nickn
amed - Black Muzzel, because he had such a heavy black moustache. Mm. And - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid294263\charrsid527797 he used to fight 'em like Billy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797  in the road.</subject2>

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 He actually fought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm, he'd fight them. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 He'd go round alone would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh he'd battle 'em, yes
, he'd get his helmet knocked off, and - there was one - notorious character there, and had a - a wooden leg and they used to call him - Peggy. And he - he was - he was very notorious, he used to get his back up against the wall and take this wooden leg o
ff - there was a - and slash at these police, before they'd get him down. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What was his job, Peggy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh he just - went around - what we called cadging. Never went to work. Mm, begging. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Your uncle, this was your mother's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 He was - a seafarer, he used to go away to sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was that very poorly paid work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It was them days, their money was eight pound a month. Eight pound a month. To go away to sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 He would have to send that back would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Well - I think they used to get what they call an allotment, they used to draw about - thirty shillings or a pound a week from the - shipping office, to live on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 How would the police - did you ever see a person so drunk that they had to be kind of hauled away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Oh yes, carried away. Or - fetch the - they used to fetch a stretcher out on two wheels with a - like a big pram like a big umbrella - shade like the - prams have got, and - got them in there and strap 'em down. If they was
 - out of hand, drunk, mad drunk. And - the women used to sit and - at the pub doors shelling peas and - doing their - Sunday mornings vegetables in the pub. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did they take children in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, the children, no, that time that - the law had
 just come out - no children allowed in the pubs. So they used to sit outside with them. On the step. And they used to wear a man's cap with a pin in it. Mm. But not - the back part of the cap there was flat, on top of the head with a big - pin pushed thr
ough, and a shawl over their shoulders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did that mark them as a bit different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Oh yes. Definitely it would. Yes, wear - Mrs Kent and I mothers never. They'd have their coat or jacket whatever it would be, and a proper hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Were there women in certain kinds of trades or jobs who wore shawls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. It was just the - the way they were - they - they - they dragged theirselves - into I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Were there any women who didn't wear hats at all, or anything on their head?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No, not - not that I - no, there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 That sounds quite same street your husband was telling me where he used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. But - even in our road there would be some of them dressed like that wouldn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 With caps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. That - Mrs Turn
 next door did didn't she. But of course our mothers wouldn't 'cos they never used to go without hats in those days, they used to wear hats didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember any gangs, street gangs or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. What do you mean, schoolchildren do you mean schoolchildren?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mr K. No. Well - I say no, they - there - there was gangs about, you see - when you're - round - no, I'm talking - you're talking about grown ups aren't you?</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 I was meaning like round the Elephant and Castle there was a thing called the Elephant gang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mr K. That's right, well just going to tell you, you see - where we lived - we lived in Canning Town. We lived in Canning Town, and - the laws of the - well, it's we - we lived - two - there wer
e - they were two wards, yes. That's right. Well Canning Town, and there was a - a border - Canning Town came under West Ham and Easter Ham - Urban District Council, but - there was a bridge - and they called it the Hine Bridge and you went over that and 
y
ou came into the City of London - not City of London - London County Council. Well the laws of the pub - in the London County Council, their pubs - opened at - we'll say just for argument's sake - seven o'clock and they kept open 'til - eleven o'clock. Se
e
? Where - in Canning known they opened at six thirty, and shut at ten thirty. So - the results were - there used to be - crowds of people - near the bridge say right, over the bridge - and - we'll soon have another half an hour and - that's when the war s
t
art, they used to have these gangs, and they used to - of course set about 'em on the bridge and rob 'em. Mm. 'Course I - I haven't been in that but I've been in the skirmish in Custom House - and I was saving up for my holidays, and I - incidentally this
 
was out of Wightman Street, and we - went to a - I went to a party there, 'cos - they were poor but I was very fond I was very fond of my old aunt because she was clean. And - she had a lot of daughters and sons I tell you, eleven of them, and I used to h
a
ve a great time there. And - I'd left there perhaps midnight and gone through this alley and I've had to return because I knew that - once I got round this corner I - I'd get - knocked down and me money taken. Yes it - it was a very - very rough quarters 
where we lived, we - we happened to be in quite a - a - a decent sort of an area.</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mrs K. I was going to say, our - our - I was going to say our part was - wasn't. Too bad at all, but - no, but up round the docks it was rough but I didn't go round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mr K. Although we had a family living opposite us, I should think there must have been about fourteen children there, name of Webbs. Mm. And they just round about the school, no s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid294263\charrsid527797 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 oes and socks and - and - their clothes were what other people liked to give them.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mrs K. Well she had one every - every year didn't she, as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. I've seen my mother call in - her little boy once going to school and it was snowing and his - trousers was torn right
 up to - used to take him in and - sew them up for him. He was so cold.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You remember the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes, they lived - almost opposite didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was it just the size of the family do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 I expect so. Yes. They had 
one every year didn't she. Always seemed - seemed to be expecting a baby you know. They were tiny man and the - the woman weren't they. Ever such a small couple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. And of course my mother was a widow - through the war - first world war - and she'
d got - four of 'em to bring up from children. I was the eldest, and of course she had quite an handful with us three boys was - first - yes, three boys, and of course we weren't very particular you can - be assured. We left her a life, dog's life. Oh no,
 but we used to be - all out pranks.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mrs K. Oh I don't know, you weren't bad. For boys, I mean good gracious me. I mean you was - he was twenty when your dad died. You was twenty when your dad died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. Yes, I was twenty. Master of 
the house then. And that's - that fell on my shoulders you see, that - that sort of thing did them days. You - if you - had any respect for your parents. Yes, I used to give nearly all my money up.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 I don't suppose everyone did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, 'cos we courted for seven years didn't we.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Were you saving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Well actually we didn't save, not for - I mean you - was looking after your mum wasn't you really and - we used to - have a good time didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. Oh yes. She was the one that - made me - start marriage, get - save up, she said, nearly time you married this girl.</subject2>

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 So you knew each other from when you moved to that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You were already there, you moved first did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, well - well you'd just - you'd only just moved there hadn't you really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Much the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm. Your eldest brother was ten months older - your eldest brother, Charles. Ten months old and he is now what - sixty -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. He's - sixty-two. I'm eight years 
old - older than him. But mind you in my parents house - mm, you see all my mother's - people were seafaring going people. And - nephews and - brothers, all in - in the Navy. And of course they - one was a - a nephew what's left home - no parents and she 
took him in. As a young man. And - he made his home there well of course - he went in the Navy and - they used to have - terrific high does at my mother's house.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 That's like you were mentioning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes. He'd bring all his pals home on leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would there be singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. Piano and everythin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998\charrsid527797 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797  going, oh yes.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998\charrsid527797 Mrs K. Well all parties in those}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
 days used to be nearly all night parties when they had parties because they had nothing else to do see, they used to make their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 How often would that be that they'd have a party like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well this used to happen every time he came home on leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mrs K. Two or three times a year. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. Well sometimes I'd 
be six months, sometimes it would be a twelve month. It depend. And - I've known him to come home on leave on a - on a ten day's - leave, with thirty golden sovereigns, on that ten day's leave, and before that ten days is up - he's been broke. All spent o
n drink.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 That must have been a lot of drink in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mr K. Mm. Oh they used to go to town. 'Cos it wouldn't be just one night, it'd be - nights and days. But - not - not rowdy, really have a good time.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 And when you were quite young would you go in to these parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. Oh I - well - Mrs Kent wouldn't, when I was a young - boy of twelve years of age, but of course it was my home.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Could you sit up late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. Oh yes, yes, I was - I - I c
ould be - remain there. I used to - make myself busy to - so as I wouldn't be put to bed. And then again -</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mrs K. My parents was probably in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It's interesting they used to stay up late, because they didn't have so much entertainment then did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, no, no, you see they had to make their own didn't they. Same as what we did really, we in our teens had to make our own didn't we.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 I think they were lucky in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well I think you got more out of life than they
 do now, you appreciate things more. If things - come to easily now I think for - the youngsters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You were saying about the milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, well, as I was saying, the present day upheaval about this school milk - we never had cows milk did we. Never.
 The only time - we had cows milk was - well - for pudding or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You mean you never had a sort of drink of milk?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, we never had it in tea, we always used condensed, couldn't afford it could they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. No. Five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998\charrsid527797  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 pence for - tuppence ha'penny a big tin.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mrs K. Of condensed milk, yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there a sort of regular order with the dairy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No. A milkman used to come round the streets with a cart didn't he - with a - churn. With a churn, and t
hen he'd have - little measures like with a long handle and dip it in the churn and put it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Like people measure out corn, that type of measure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well, similar, had a - round handle on it you see, they dip it in the churn well then you'd have to 
take a jug and - half a pint or a pint, whatever you had. But - if - if you didn't get it off of him well then you'd have to go to the dairy yourself with a jug and get it. But that was only used for - like such as milk puddings and things like that. We n
ever ever drank milk did we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. No, it was tupence a pint.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Mrs K. And - and of course never - never had it at school. And then another thing I remember was - some children that - I mean they stayed to school dinners here. Well ther
e was such a thing in those days, but - it only consisted of a - bowl of soup, which I can remember was made in the playground in a - big copper. And it was a ha'penny a bowl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you have some yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, only once, I kept worrying mother to stay and - oh I didn't want to go a second time, it was like a lot of ditchwater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 But any child was eligible for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes, if you wanted to stay, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mr K. Poor. They had got to be very poor.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Even to pay the ha'penny, but you were surely not poor enough to qualify?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no. No, I don't - no, I don't - I don't think they did for any could stay if you wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there anything else with it, a bit of bread or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 I don't know, I can't remember that.
 May have been. I only stayed the once. I thought I'd be - as big as the others I suppose, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there anything else that came to your mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I - just thought of those two items when you was asking about - how the children went on
 and that, I mean we didn't - come under that - really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you ever remember ever hearing anybody described as a real lady or a real gentleman, that phrase being used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Supposing it was used, what at that time do you think it meant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well, I suppose anybody with money to our idea would be wouldn't it, I should think so
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 At that time were you aware that it was possible to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Not when we were children such a thing wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What about when you were first at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You became charge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998\charrsid527797 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 hand at that job, how long were you charge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998\charrsid527797 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 hand there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. Well - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998\charrsid527797 You had to teach}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797  these girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 And you say it was a terrible job to learn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, it was very hard to - to really get - to do it properly you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998\charrsid527797 
 know, and - I suppose about ei}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
ghteen months, two years I may have been - a forelady I suppose they called it wouldn't they. And then I found that - well these youngsters was earning more than what I was with all the worry o
f teaching them and I - worried him 'til he put me back on my own machine you see. So then I went back - yes, went back piece work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 And you stayed in that job 'til you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh after I got married. Yes, about - two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Then you stopped two years after you got married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You got married in 1926?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Six, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 When you stopped did you go back later on to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I - I stopped when I - found I was pregnant with the first baby and - of course I never worked any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 So that was the end of your paid work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Well really yes, but - when the girls got old - well - when they - left school, before they left school I was working at home, needle working. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What were you doing that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well, for money to send them to - commercial college. That's where they got their - shorthand typing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 They both went there did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you sell them to a shop or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, I did them for firms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Had you ever had any training in that or did you teach yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, actually - I was always interested in needlework and I used to make the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16008182\charrsid527797 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 s clothes, hats and coats and what have you. I went to a - when they were small I went to a - school - run by
 the council - the dressmaking classes in the afternoon and there was a nursery there for the children 'til - until they went to school theirselves. So - I was always interested in needlework you see 'cos I was a good needle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16008182\charrsid527797 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 worker at school, I'd been pick
ed to make the headmistress's nightdresses, but - all by hand of course, at school, all pin tucks. And - then - I - so that was during this last war, I saw this in the paper - anybody handy with a needle, smokers was wanted, any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16008182\charrsid527797 body was hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 y - handy with 
a needle would be taught. Or be shown. And - that was at Ilford and I went there and - I suppose I had - half hour, no more if it was that, just watching a person doing the smoking, and - she gave me some to bring away and from then on - I picked it up. A
 bit difficult at first but I got away with it and I worked for several firms.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 How many years did you keep on with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no, before - longer than that. Oh over a period of six or seven years I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you start at the beginning of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, more towards the end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 About from 1943, 44?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 After that, was that the last money you earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I - I went to a friend of mine had a restaurant in - the City. And I went to help her out, started - helping her w
ith - coffees and sort of things like that and the washing up and then - from that - I did veg cooking and from that I went to cook, and I worked there 'til she sold out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Always working for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Could you tell me roughly when it was you started there? Was it after you finished the smocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes. But smocking went out didn't it. Smocking went right out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 In about 1952 a friend of you suggested that you go and help her in her restaurant. You made coffee, did the vegetables, wa
ited at table, washed up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Over that period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 And about the last four years you were cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Then after about two weeks at home, that restaurant having closed up, the person you'd been working for before opened a factory and you to
ok work there as a finisher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You worked there full time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Until 1962 when you moved down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Then in 1963 you were asked to take a job cooking from about nine to three, and you kept on with that 'til 1965. About two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 That would be 1966, I - I was sixty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No apple picking or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no. I think I've done my share.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would you have preferred another type of occupation? Have you ever had a feeling t
here was some particular kind of work you'd not done which you'd like to have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I certainly would have liked a - to have had the education to have got an office job. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was that why you were particularly keen for your daughters to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes, I - I was determined they weren't - would - wouldn't work in a factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you like the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Not even in the first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh I had some very nice friends, but there were some very rough characters as well. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did they have any kind of initiation ceremonies or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there not a sort of a lot of coarse joking and that type of thing that some girls rather suffered from in factories?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I don't think so. There was - some that were very - used to swear a lot which - I don't - I - I don't believe in swearing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It troubled you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you belong to any trade union during your working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, we did - did have a union there. General Workers Union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you have to belong or did you join by free choice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, choice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 That was in the rubber company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you take part in activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 While you were working there did you feel that employers and wo
rkers had the same interests or that they were opposed in their sort of outlook and interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I don't we give that much consideration.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You didn't think about the workers on one hand and the bosses on the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you feel that there was a great division between craftsmen and workers, people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16008182\charrsid527797 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 ho didn't have a trade or craft when you were - a working person yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well no, that didn't enter - into it in those sort of places. Not among girls, I mean be different with men wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It didn't come into your work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would you say that working full time changed your attitude, outlook on life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, we just took those things for granted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 I wondered whether you felt you sort of got more experience of life and things through working or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
No. Not that it - I don't think it did us any harm - to work hard, I mean - we've always - worked hard but I don't think we're any the worse for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You were fourteen when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
That leaves a few years left of the period after you left school, about four years. In those years can you tell me how you spent your leisure time, work finished, you'd come home and have your tea and then what would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Which four years, when I first left school? Well, no, I used to - up 'til - eighteen - I just come home from work and - what leisure I did have I was - used to read, mostly, I never went out. I might the last - well - year I suppose, about - I was about
 seventeen, go out with a girlfriend, now and again but - most time was spent at home, working, helping with the work and washing and what have you after I come home. Always had to work at home. Although we worked twelve hours a day. But of course - those
 hours altered. Before the end of the - first world war they all - they - they - the new factory act came in and we worked half past seven 'til five then. Was it after the war? Oh. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you ever go to dances up to the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you make any new friends while you were at work? Did you have sort of new girl friends or boy friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 I never had any boyfriends. I had - one or two girlfriends but I always kept to the same ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Were they school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16008182\charrsid527797 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 They were girls you got to know after leaving work. Did you ever go on holiday with your girlfriends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. I went one year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you go with your own money and that sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes. And we never got paid holidays so we used 
to have to - save up and - pay for it and also pay for - pay our mother although we went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 So that was quite a financial struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. Oh yes, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Where did you go for your holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well, that time I went to Hove, near Brighton for - an aunt of mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 That was the first time you saw the sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, I went with my father before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 This time when you went to Hove to the aunt was that after the war then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 These two particular girl friends you had, I think you said there were two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did your parents know their families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Had they ever come to your house, those girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. Mm. One was courting, her boyfriend, I don't know I think - if I can remember rightly was on
 a farm but - she was taken ill and she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Quite suddenly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, she had meningitis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you have to be home by a certain time if you went out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. Ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was that quite strictly enforced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Were you ever late?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Not when I had girl friends. I - I did when I had a boyfriend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 But that was a bit later on was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes, but I used to get told - and told off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 With your girlfriends did you ever go up to the West End at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes. Theatres now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you ever sort of go up there for any other reason, shopping or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No. Went up there to see one or two shows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Anything else about that period of your life that you remember which you say took a new interest in or sort of changed in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would you say reading was one of your main pastimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You enjoyed Dickens didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Any other sort of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well any book that I can get hold of I used to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Where did you get them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Library.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was there quite a good library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, but we used to - buy a lot of books and exchange them you know like a - sort of a li - a book club thing. Among the girls - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 What about magazines, did you get any magazines of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No, we didn't read magazines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It was novels mainly was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm, mostly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 During that period did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember having any views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you think you'd have followed your parents at that stage or not? Could you tell me anything about your political awareness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well, no, I didn't - I didn't take any interest in politics, for one thi
ng you weren't allowed to vote were you 'til you were twenty-one, so - you wouldn't interest yourself in it would you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You said you remembered your father sounding off about Lloyd George?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh yes, he was - proper Labour, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 But you didn't sort of get involved yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 When you were out did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 If you went out for an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh - say where you went, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 So starting work didn't mean complete independence in that sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you continue to - you said you used to teach at Sunday school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you continue to go to the service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would you say that starting full time work made any differ
ent to the way you were treated at home, your relationship with your parents or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 You were still treated the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Can you remember how your parents expected you to behave towards your brothers and you sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Well no, only looking after them when they weren't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember if you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16008182\charrsid527797 quarrelled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698785\charrsid527797  ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh I suppose we did, we had our quarrels. What sisters don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Do you remember your parents taking any particular line on that, if they were particularly bothered about quarrelling or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It's not something that stands out in your mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 All right, but of course they were all younger than me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Your sisters were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
Yes. And my two brothers, well of course one - they went to the war of course - the eldest one was - in the Territorials, well he was only seventeen - when the war started and of course - he had to go straight away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Was he the one who died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
No. No. He was the one - he was eighteen when he got called up. You had to go when you was eighteen. And - he did just a year and he was taken to France and that was it, he was nineteen when he was killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did you have any sort of funeral service or anything when that happened?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Of course it was in France?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, he was missing you see and - presumed killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Did the news come by telegram, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, I suppose it did in those days. Come to think of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 It wasn't broken by a minister or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Would you say of your brothers and sisters was there one you were particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Yes, the sister next to me. There's five yea
rs between us you see because - the other two had died as I told you, as babies. And we were close, well we were the only two left we were. Until - just before I married. She's the last one and she died with cancer. Yes we were close 'cos we were the only
 two girls left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865103 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 Anything else that sort of comes to mind that I haven't covered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339325 LK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698785\charrsid527797 
No, only asking about - you asking about - having to get a - in by a certain time, well that - really - went on 'til we got married, really, which I was twenty-five then.
